~ start
Willomena Wanderweave: (fainter now — you can see the rock through her — and she does not rise) Oh. You're still here. You followed. Good.
Willomena Wanderweave: I'm tired, little weaver. Will you remember the flower for me? When you find it. Just... remember it. That's all I ask.
Willomena Wanderweave: (another page settles at your feet, the ink still wet) Read it later. Or don't.
Willomena Wanderweave: [i][wave amp=20 freq=3]"I have been here longer than I have been alive. That should not be possible. But in the Meadows, the impossible is only what hasn't happened yet."[/wave][/i]
=> END
